{
  "quotes": [
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0001",
      "block_id": "B114",
      "text": "to date, and in an effort to maximize value for Mac-Gray's stockholders, the Special Committee instructed BofA Merrill Lynch to call each of Party A, Party B, Party C and CSC/Pamplona to request final indications of interest by September 18, 2013 and to indicate that Mac-Gray would consider engaging in a short period of exclusive negotiations with one of the bidders depending upon, among"
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0002",
      "block_id": "B007",
      "text": "industry-wide merger and acquisition activity and dynamics, and authorized Mac-Gray management to work with BofA Merrill Lynch to explore transactional opportunities that might be available to"
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0003",
      "block_id": "B009",
      "text": "between Party A and Mac-Gray. During this call, the representative of Party A indicated that Party A might consider a business combination with Mac-Gray."
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0004",
      "block_id": "B036",
      "text": "On May 31, 2013, Mac-Gray entered into an engagement letter with BofA Merrill Lynch with respect to the Board's undertaking a review of strategic"
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0005",
      "block_id": "B040",
      "text": "June 21, 2013, Party A submitted an unsolicited proposal to the Mac-Gray Board of Directors offering to purchase Mac-Gray for an all-cash purchase price of $17.00 to $19.00 per"
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0006",
      "block_id": "B040",
      "text": "June 21, 2013, Party A submitted an unsolicited proposal to the Mac-Gray Board of Directors offering to purchase Mac-Gray for an all-cash purchase price of $17.00 to $19.00 per share, which we refer to as the Party A June 21 proposal."
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0007",
      "block_id": "B042",
      "text": "the Board then established the Special Committee, comprised of the six independent and disinterested members of the Board (namely, Mr. Bullock, Mr. Daoust, Mr. Hyman, William F. Meagher, Bruce A. Percelay and Alastair G. Robinson), to, among other things, explore strategic alternatives to enhance value to Mac-Gray's stockholders and to recommend to the Board the advisability of any such strategic alternative."
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0008",
      "block_id": "B057",
      "text": "on June 28, 2013, Party B, entered into a confidentiality and standstill agreement with Mac-Gray and was provided with an informational package for the purpose of providing"
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0009",
      "block_id": "B059",
      "text": "June 30, 2013, Party C entered into a confidentiality and standstill agreement with Mac-Gray and was provided with an informational package for the purpose of providing Party C"
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0010",
      "block_id": "B067",
      "text": "July 11, 2013, CSC/Pamplona entered into a confidentiality and standstill agreement with Mac-Gray and were provided with an informational package for the purpose of providing"
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0011",
      "block_id": "B071",
      "text": "July 23, 2013, CSC/Pamplona submitted a preliminary indication of interest at an all-cash purchase price of $18.50 per share."
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0012",
      "block_id": "B073",
      "text": "July 24, 2013, Party B submitted a preliminary indication of interest at an all-cash purchase price of $17.00 to $18.00 per share. Also on July 24, 2013, representatives"
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0013",
      "block_id": "B073",
      "text": "from Party C called BofA Merrill Lynch and presented an oral preliminary indication of interest at an all-cash purchase price of $15.00 to $17.00 per share."
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0014",
      "block_id": "B081",
      "text": "on July 25, 2013, Party C submitted a written indication of interest at an all-cash purchase price of $16.00 to $16.50 per share."
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0015",
      "block_id": "B083",
      "text": "August 5, 2013, Party A entered into a confidentiality and standstill agreement with Mac-Gray and was provided with an informational package for the purpose of providing Party A with data to"
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0016",
      "block_id": "B106",
      "text": "September 9, 2013, CSC/Pamplona submitted a revised indication of interest with an all-cash purchase price of $19.50 per share, indicating that Pamplona was committed to"
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0017",
      "block_id": "B106",
      "text": "September 9, 2013, CSC/Pamplona submitted a revised indication of interest with an all-cash purchase price of $19.50 per share, indicating that Pamplona was committed to provide 100% of the capital required to consummate the transaction and requesting that CSC/Pamplona and Mac-Gray agree to exclusive negotiations for two weeks. On September 9, 2013, Party B"
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0018",
      "block_id": "B106",
      "text": "provide 100% of the capital required to consummate the transaction and requesting that CSC/Pamplona and Mac-Gray agree to exclusive negotiations for two weeks. On September 9, 2013, Party B also submitted a revised indication of interest with an all-cash purchase price of $18.50 per share and proposed to finance the transaction with a combination of equity from affiliated funds and third"
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0019",
      "block_id": "B106",
      "text": "party debt. Party B's revised indication of interest did not include a firm financing commitment."
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0020",
      "block_id": "B108",
      "text": "September 10, 2013, Party A submitted a revised indication of interest with an all-cash purchase price of $18.00 to $19.00 per share, to be financed by outstanding credit"
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0021",
      "block_id": "B108",
      "text": "a revised oral indication of interest with an all-cash purchase price of $16.00 to $17.00 per share. Neither Party A's nor Party C's revised indication of interest included a firm financing"
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0022",
      "block_id": "B120",
      "text": "September 18, 2013, CSC/Pamplona submitted a proposal for an all-cash purchase price of $20.75 per share, reiterating that Pamplona was committed to provide 100% of the capital"
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0023",
      "block_id": "B120",
      "text": "September 18, 2013, CSC/Pamplona submitted a proposal for an all-cash purchase price of $20.75 per share, reiterating that Pamplona was committed to provide 100% of the capital required to consummate the transaction and requesting that CSC/Pamplona and Mac-Gray agree to engage in exclusive negotiations for two weeks. Also on September 18, 2013, Party A reiterated in a"
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0024",
      "block_id": "B120",
      "text": "telephone call to a representative of BofA Merrill Lynch that its previous indication of interest with an all-cash purchase price of $18.00 to $19.00 per share was its best and final offer. On"
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0025",
      "block_id": "B120",
      "text": "September 18, 2013, Party B also submitted a revised indication of interest with a purchase price that Party B valued at $21.50 per share, including $19.00 of cash to be paid at closing"
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0026",
      "block_id": "B120",
      "text": "September 18, 2013, Party B also submitted a revised indication of interest with a purchase price that Party B valued at $21.50 per share, including $19.00 of cash to be paid at closing"
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0027",
      "block_id": "B120",
      "text": "and the remaining per share price to be paid in the form of options to be issued to Mac-Gray stockholders, representing 10% of the new equity with a strike price equal to Party B's initial cost basis."
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0028",
      "block_id": "B120",
      "text": "excluding any future acquisitions. Party B's proposal stated that it valued the Party B options at $2.50 of incremental value per share. Party C did not submit a revised indication of interest or reiterate its prior indication of interest of an all-cash purchase price of $16.00 to $17.00 per share nor did it specify any reasons in connection therewith."
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0029",
      "block_id": "B128",
      "text": "the Transaction Committee to confirm that CSC/Pamplona were willing to increase their all-cash purchase price to $21.25 per share as a last and best offer, provided that Mac-Gray agree to a two week"
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0030",
      "block_id": "B177",
      "text": "in the day, on October 14, 2013, the merger agreement was executed, the Pamplona commitment letter was delivered, Moab and Parent executed the Moab voting agreement and the"
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0031",
      "block_id": "B179",
      "text": "October 15, 2013, before the U. S. stock markets opened, Mac-Gray and CSC jointly announced the execution of the merger agreement."
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0032",
      "block_id": "B003",
      "text": "The Mac-Gray Board of Directors, whom we sometimes to refer to as the Board, and Mac-Gray's management have continually engaged in a"
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0033",
      "block_id": "B017",
      "text": "meeting, which we refer to as the Transaction Committee, and appointed Thomas Bullock and Paul Daoust, both independent directors, to serve as its members. Mr. Daoust was appointed because of"
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0034",
      "block_id": "B042",
      "text": "alternatives, the Board then established the Special Committee, comprised of the six independent and disinterested members of the Board (namely, Mr. Bullock, Mr. Daoust,"
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0035",
      "block_id": "B005",
      "text": "CSC, which we refer to as the 2011-2012 Discussions, Mac-Gray engaged BofA Merrill Lynch on October 23, 2012. During the fall and winter of 2012, CSC engaged in a sale process and, ultimately,"
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0036",
      "block_id": "B011",
      "text": "secretary, and representatives from BofA Merrill Lynch and Goodwin Procter LLP, outside legal counsel to Mac-Gray, were also in attendance for all or portions of the meeting. At this meeting,"
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0037",
      "block_id": "B140",
      "text": "September 25, 2013, Goodwin Procter delivered to Kirkland & Ellis LLP, outside legal counsel to CSC/Pamplona, whom we refer to as Kirkland, the initial draft of"
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0038",
      "block_id": "B007",
      "text": "Mac-Gray, including opportunities with another strategic party, whom we refer to as Party A, in the laundry facilities management industry. The Board also determined to further consider Mac-Gray's"
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0039",
      "block_id": "B057",
      "text": "on June 28, 2013, Party B, entered into a confidentiality and standstill agreement with Mac-Gray and was provided with an informational package for the purpose of providing"
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0040",
      "block_id": "B059",
      "text": "June 30, 2013, Party C entered into a confidentiality and standstill agreement with Mac-Gray and was provided with an informational package for the purpose of providing Party C"
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0041",
      "block_id": "B051",
      "text": "including CSC and Pamplona, who together we refer to as CSC/Pamplona, and Party A, to solicit potential interest in a transaction with Mac-Gray, 15 of which were potential strategic"
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0042",
      "block_id": "B034",
      "text": "E. Hyman, candidates nominated by Mac-Gray's stockholder, Moab Partners, L. P. and certain of its affiliates, which we refer collectively to as Moab. Mac-Gray and Moab engaged in a proxy contest"
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0043",
      "block_id": "B177",
      "text": "in the day, on October 14, 2013, the merger agreement was executed, the Pamplona commitment letter was delivered, Moab and Parent executed the Moab voting agreement and the"
    }
